{
  "doc_id": "29244",
  "text": "Multidrug resistant bacteria producing carbapenemases such as New Delhi metallo-beta-lactamase-1 (NDM-1) have been reported in Asian countries in every clinical setting, including CAP [CITATION_1] . In China, 2% of 208 K. pneumoniae isolates from 12 hospitals produced carbapenemases [CITATION_2] . Carbapenemase-producing K. pneumoniae isolates from various samples were also detected in South Korea, in Singapore and in Taiwan [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . In Thailand NDM-1-producing K. pneumoniae isolates were reported from urinary samples [CITATION_6] . Our review did not show any report of carbapenemase-producing enterobacteriaceae to December 2012 in Cambodia and neighboring countries in respiratory samples. Only strains of K. pneumoniae resistant to amoxicillin-clavulanic acid and to third-generation cephalosporins were responsible for CAP. The emergence of multidrug resistant enterobacteriaceae should be closely monitored.",
